Title : William Thornhill
Text : {{short description|16th-century English politician}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}
{{Use British English|date=December 2017}}
'''William Thornhill''' (c. 1500 – 21 August 1557), of Thornhill in [[Stalbridge]], [[Dorset]], was an English politician.

==Family==
Thornhill was the eldest son of Thomas Thornhill of Thornhill and his wife Joan née Hussey, daughter of Thomas Hussey of [[Shapwick, Dorset|Shapwick]]. William married twice: firstly to a daughter of William Chauncy of [[Charlton, Brinkworth|Charlton]] in Wiltshire, by whom he had two sons and three daughters; secondly to Joan Brydges, daughter of Henry Brydges of [[Newbury, Berkshire|Newbury]], [[Berkshire]].

==Career==
He was a [[Member of Parliament|Member]] (MP) of the [[Parliament of England]] for [[Poole (UK Parliament constituency)|Poole]] in 1529.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1509-1558/member/thornhill-william-1500-57|title=THORNHILL, William (by 1500-57), of Thornhill in Stalbridge, Dorset|publisher=The History of Parliament|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>

